{{Refimprove|date=June 2010}} {{Infobox Organization |name = Association for the Conservation of Energy |image = |size = |caption = |abbreviation = UKACE |motto = |formation = 1981 |extinction = |status = [[Non-profit organization]] |purpose = Energy conservation in the UK |location = Westgate House, 2a Prebend Street, London, N1 8PT |region_served = UK |membership = 24 UK companies |leader_title = Director |leader_name = Andrew Warren |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |budget = |website = [http://www.ukace.org UKACE] |remarks = }}
The '''Association for the Conservation of Energy''' is a British organisation that promotes [[energy conservation]]. It represents the energy conservation industry and does collective research for the industry. The Association for the Conservation of Energy was formed in 1981 and Andrew Warren has been the Director since its formation. It is based in the east of the [[London Borough of Islington]].
==Structure and membership==
The Association for the Conservation of Energy has two divisions: * Research unit, which does the (scientific) examination of ways of conserving energy, and keeping up-to-date of the rapidly changing technology. * Parliamentary campaigns, which operates on a national level to influence [[energy policy]].
Members include: * [[Cavity Insulation Guarantee Agency]] (based in [[Leighton Buzzard]]) * [[Dow Chemical Company|Dow Chemical Ltd]] * [[E.ON UK]] (based in Coventry) * [[Knauf Insulation]] (based in [[St Helens, Merseyside|St Helens]]) * [[Pilkington]] (based in St Helens) * [http://www.rockwool.co.uk Rockwool] (based in [[Pencoed]]) * [[Scottish Power]] * [[SIG plc]] * [http://www.ursa-uk.co.uk Ursa] (a Spanish insulation company)
==See also== * [[Energy Institute]] * [[The Carbon Trust]] * [[Energy Saving Trust]] * [[Efficient energy use]] * [[Renewable energy commercialization]]
