{{italic title}} The '''''Nomina Anatomica Veterinaria''''' (often abbreviated as '''''NAV''''') is a text prepared by the International Committee on Veterinary Gross Anatomical Nomenclature. It is used as the standard reference for [[anatomy|anatomical]] ([[Zootomy|zootomical]]) terminology in the field of [[Veterinary medicine|Veterinary Science]].
The text is continually under revision. The 5th edition is available free of charge from the World Association of Veterinary Anatomists (WAVA)<ref>[http://www.wava-amav.org/index.html ''World Association of Veterinary Anatomists (WAVA)'']</ref> as a [[Portable Document Format|PDF]] file,<ref>[http://www.wava-amav.org/wava-documents.html ''Nomina'', 6th Edition- Revised 2017]</ref> with last revision in 2017. The 6th edition has not been printed commercially. The 4th edition, published in 1994,<ref name="isbn0-9600444-7-7">{{cite book |author= |title=''Nomina Anatomica Veterinaria'' |publisher=The Committees |location=Zürich |year=1994 |pages= |edition=4th |isbn=0-9600444-7-7 |oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref> was the last commercially printed edition.
==See also== * ''[[Nomina Anatomica]]''
